  <refentry xml:id="function.socket-close" xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
   <refnamediv>
    <refname>socket_close</refname>
    <refpurpose>Fecha um socket resource</refpurpose>
   </refnamediv>
   <refsect1>
    <title>Descrição</title>
     <methodsynopsis>
      <type>void</type><methodname>socket_close</methodname>
      <methodparam><type>resource</type><parameter>socket</parameter></methodparam>
     </methodsynopsis>
    &warn.experimental.func;
    <para>
     <function>socket_close</function> fecha o socket resource
     dado por <parameter>socket</parameter>.
    </para>
    <note>
     <para>
      <function>socket_close</function> não pode ser usado  em arquivos PHP file resources
      criados com <function>fopen</function>, <function>popen</function>,
      <function>fsockopen</function>, ou <function>pfsockopen</function>; isso serve
      parapara sockets criados com <function>socket_create</function> ou
      <function>socket_accept</function>.
     </para>
    </note>
    <para>
     Veja também <function>socket_bind</function>, <function>socket_listen</function>,
     <function>socket_create</function> e
     <function>socket_strerror</function>.
    </para>
   </refsect1>
  </refentry>

